In the Philippines, "Filipino" is typically considered to be gender-neutral, hence its usage as an umbrella term here. In the United States, terms like "Filipinx" (patterned off of "Latinx") have recently cropped up, but they are not nearly as widely in use as terms such as "Latinx" or "Latine".
